description:
We all know that Seventh-day Adventist schools have no classes on the Sabbath. Children, teachers, and administrators have good discipline. They have high academic standards and rank. They also have adequate facilities for students' learning, as other schools do. So, do we still need Adventist schools around? What makes Adventist schools so unique?

There are numerous reasons why Adventist schools differ from other institutions in terms of teachers, curriculum, and so on. Watch the video to find out what makes Adventist schools special and why we should send our children there.

https://youtu.be/UyrgbgI9hDQ


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are believers who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing, and hope in Jesus.

Want to learn more about the Seventh-day Adventist Church? 
Visit our website at: https://www.adventist.org/
